Chocolate Chia Pudding  - gf, dairy-free
  --Molly Baz

7 oz medjool dates (~13) pitted
3 c unsweetened cashew milk
2/3 c raw cashews
3 tbsp cocoa powder
2 tsp vanilla extrace
1 1/2 tsp kosher salt
1 tsp ground cinnamon
1/2 c white chia seeds

Blend everything except chia seeds in a blender on high until very smooth, ~1 min. Transfer to an air tight container, stir in chia seeds and refrigerate at least 6 hrs, preferrably overnight. Can be made up to 5 days in advance.

Notes: can use almond milk (or any nut milks really) also can use black chia in place of white.
